                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.796/9–2744</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Canadian Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="88" xml:id="d459fn88">The Department acknowledged this memorandum on
                        October 6, 1944.</note>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Exploratory discussions between officials of the governments of the British
                    Commonwealth will take place in Canada in the latter part of October to consider
                    operational and technical problems connected with possible air routes between
                    the members of the Commonwealth. These discussions were agreed upon, though not
                    announced, before <pb facs="0557" n="547" xml:id="pg_547"/> the Government of
                    the United States issued its invitations to an international conference on civil
                    aviation. It is felt by the Commonwealth governments that these discussions
                    between their officials on a non-committal basis will be helpful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-27">September 27,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
